WEBVTT

00:02.200 --> 00:04.758
There is a darkness hangs
over the House of Capulet.

00:05.447 --> 00:06.950
Paris has proposed.

00:06.984 --> 00:08.742
Does Lady Capulet know of your plans?

00:08.775 --> 00:10.310
[Sighs] She's a sweet girl.

00:10.343 --> 00:11.942
And you're going to make her a Princess.

00:11.976 --> 00:13.733
- Escalus is weak.
- Aye.

00:13.768 --> 00:16.389
No price should be too high
to take his place.

00:17.384 --> 00:19.493
I must warn you.
Montague will seek his revenge,

00:19.528 --> 00:20.742
and there will be war.

00:20.776 --> 00:22.564
Then let it be war.

00:23.440 --> 00:24.956
Escalus: Benvolio Montague.

00:24.990 --> 00:27.194
He calls himself
the New Prince of Verona.

00:27.227 --> 00:28.910
Is this true?

00:30.576 --> 00:31.630
Is it?

00:32.976 --> 00:34.062
Yes.

00:36.080 --> 00:38.894
♪♪

00:46.288 --> 00:49.070
Count Paris: Whatever that is,
it can't be good for your city.

00:49.104 --> 00:51.406
Whatever that is
will soon be smoothed over

00:51.440 --> 00:52.942
once justice is served.

00:59.023 --> 01:00.653
She's home!

01:00.687 --> 01:02.413
Lady Rosaline's home!

01:06.895 --> 01:08.524
Rosaline!

01:08.559 --> 01:09.741
Livia!

01:11.694 --> 01:12.621
[Chuckles]

01:12.654 --> 01:13.612
You're here.

01:13.647 --> 01:15.094
I was so worried...

01:15.129 --> 01:16.374
Are you all right? Tell me.

01:16.409 --> 01:17.968
Me? Of course.

01:18.003 --> 01:20.565
I haven't slept a night since
that hateful Montague took you,

01:20.606 --> 01:23.515
but now that you're home, safe...

01:23.549 --> 01:26.043
You can rest easy, gentle Livia,

01:26.077 --> 01:28.187
and dream sweet dreams once more.

01:28.220 --> 01:31.920
Thank you, Count Paris.
With all my heart.

01:32.092 --> 01:34.714
[Footsteps approaching]

01:35.391 --> 01:36.605
Count Paris.

01:36.639 --> 01:38.397
You're home!

01:38.431 --> 01:40.317
We owe you a great debt.

01:40.351 --> 01:41.565
Let us celebrate...

01:41.599 --> 01:43.196
Livia, run and tell the cook

01:43.230 --> 01:45.565
that we have a hero at our table today.

01:46.302 --> 01:48.188
[Chuckles]

01:48.222 --> 01:50.300
Livia, wait...

01:50.334 --> 01:52.156
[Sighs]

01:52.190 --> 01:55.036
♪♪

01:57.630 --> 01:58.812
You're back.

02:00.516 --> 02:01.634
I am.

02:03.826 --> 02:05.679
I thank the Lord for your safe return.

02:05.714 --> 02:08.976
♪♪

02:13.330 --> 02:17.571
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

02:17.798 --> 02:20.100
And from the dark there came a cry,

02:20.134 --> 02:22.564
and I saw her running towards us
on the road...

02:22.598 --> 02:25.604
risking her life to escape
from that Montague devil.

02:25.638 --> 02:27.364
Were you not terribly afraid?

02:28.518 --> 02:30.404
If she was, she never showed it.

02:30.438 --> 02:32.356
Benvolio Montague, on the other hand...

02:32.390 --> 02:34.276
wept like a child when we caught him.

02:34.310 --> 02:36.772
Had I only known...

02:36.805 --> 02:38.492
I am truly sorry, niece,

02:38.527 --> 02:40.327
to have betrothed you to that monster.

02:41.520 --> 02:43.245
When will he be executed?

02:43.280 --> 02:45.198
That's up to the Crown, of course.

02:45.231 --> 02:47.245
I wish him little time left
on this Earth.

02:47.279 --> 02:49.069
[Liquid pouring]

02:51.532 --> 02:53.835
Come, Livia. Let's fetch dessert.

02:53.868 --> 02:55.306
Don't be silly. I can manage...

02:55.340 --> 02:58.058
No. I insist...

02:58.092 --> 03:01.644
You must still be fatigued
from your ordeal, my Lady.

03:01.678 --> 03:02.890
Sit.

03:03.667 --> 03:04.970
Please.

03:05.490 --> 03:07.194
My Lord, there's a carriage

03:07.235 --> 03:08.320
for Lady Rosaline.

03:08.355 --> 03:09.184
From the palace.

03:09.218 --> 03:12.385
♪♪

03:14.011 --> 03:15.610
Tessa: Capulet's doing.

03:15.644 --> 03:17.882
Lord Montague: This church
was to be our legacy.

03:18.660 --> 03:20.505
The Montagues' mark upon the world.

03:20.921 --> 03:24.438
Generations of toil
destroyed overnight...

03:24.472 --> 03:27.062
How dare he?

03:27.097 --> 03:29.079
This is war, Damiano.

03:29.113 --> 03:31.991
For once, little sister,

03:32.024 --> 03:33.751
we're in agreement.

03:33.784 --> 03:36.023
My Lord.

03:36.056 --> 03:37.523
Benvolio's been captured.

03:37.571 --> 03:39.105
Alive?

03:41.129 --> 03:43.207
She's of little consequence.

03:43.241 --> 03:45.638
Little consequence?
She knows everything.

03:45.673 --> 03:47.366
Which means Benvolio does, too.

03:48.937 --> 03:50.407
He'll be dead soon enough...

03:50.440 --> 03:53.158
it's in the Crown's interest
not to ask too many questions.

03:53.558 --> 03:55.252
But my control over Rosaline's tongue

03:55.286 --> 03:56.851
- won't last long...
- I said no.

03:58.262 --> 03:59.540
[Sighs]

03:59.573 --> 04:01.460
It was a mistake to wish her dead.

04:03.413 --> 04:05.587
Juliet loved Rosaline.

04:05.622 --> 04:08.084
I know [Sighs]

04:08.118 --> 04:10.164
I feel...

04:10.197 --> 04:12.980
my daughter wouldn't want me
to take her friend's life.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.947
"No matter the cost."

04:17.540 --> 04:19.682
That's what you said when Juliet died...

04:19.716 --> 04:21.697
if I took Escalus off the throne,

04:21.731 --> 04:23.330
and wiped the Montagues off the map,

04:23.363 --> 04:24.738
it would be worth it,

04:24.771 --> 04:26.945
no matter the cost.

04:27.277 --> 04:28.587
Juliet is dead, my Lady.

04:28.621 --> 04:31.084
But Rosaline isn't,
and she knows too much.

04:31.117 --> 04:33.163
I can't keep her mouth shut much longer.

04:33.197 --> 04:35.659
And I'm sure if your daughter
still walked this Earth,

04:35.694 --> 04:37.886
she wouldn't want you hanged
for treason.

04:39.630 --> 04:42.027
Take heart, it won't be much longer now.

04:42.061 --> 04:44.298
Our army of Fiends keeps
your House and the Montagues

04:44.333 --> 04:46.444
at each other's throats.

04:46.477 --> 04:48.587
You saw what happened
to the cathedral...

04:48.621 --> 04:51.178
how long before Montague
takes his revenge?

04:51.213 --> 04:52.683
And on, and on,

04:52.717 --> 04:54.124
until the thought of this city

04:54.157 --> 04:55.915
taking up arms against a common enemy

04:55.949 --> 04:59.403
is as unthinkable as Venice
sinking into the sea.

04:59.437 --> 05:00.747
[Door opens]

05:01.376 --> 05:04.254
My father always said Verona is a flower

05:04.288 --> 05:06.174
waiting to be picked...

05:06.208 --> 05:08.062
and now, thanks to us,

05:08.096 --> 05:10.460
the garden gate is open.

05:11.103 --> 05:13.440
- My Lord, I was just looking for you.
- Lord Capulet: Oh.

05:13.474 --> 05:15.293
There's something I've been
meaning to ask...

05:15.328 --> 05:16.861
[Indistinct chatter]

05:16.896 --> 05:18.910
Man: Make way, you.

05:18.943 --> 05:20.221
[Grunting]

05:20.255 --> 05:22.525
♪♪

05:28.954 --> 05:30.136
Escalus: Thank you for coming.

05:32.249 --> 05:34.192
You wished to speak alone...

05:35.577 --> 05:36.653
I did.

05:40.793 --> 05:42.264
I do.

05:43.034 --> 05:45.175
I never thought
I'd see you in my room again.

05:46.763 --> 05:49.045
Now that we're alone, Your Grace,

05:49.079 --> 05:50.139
I must speak freely...

05:50.173 --> 05:51.559
No.

05:51.584 --> 05:53.502
It is I who must speak freely.

05:54.714 --> 05:56.696
For I have been a fool.

05:56.730 --> 05:58.296
What...

05:58.329 --> 06:00.728
And if I have learned nothing
from these endless days,

06:00.762 --> 06:03.054
when I knew not
whether you were alive or dead,

06:03.769 --> 06:05.807
whether I'd ever see your face again...

06:08.055 --> 06:09.529
Hmm.

06:09.797 --> 06:12.387
I love you, Rosaline Capulet.

06:12.422 --> 06:14.467
I've <i> always</i> loved you,

06:14.900 --> 06:18.243
and I beg your forgiveness
for everything I've done.

06:18.820 --> 06:21.251
I have hurt you,
and I have lied to you...

06:21.285 --> 06:22.979
And I have lied to you.

06:24.634 --> 06:26.776
When I said that the Montague
kidnapped me.

06:26.810 --> 06:29.560
When I said that Paris rescued me...

06:29.594 --> 06:31.041
those were lies.

06:32.667 --> 06:34.296
What?

06:34.828 --> 06:37.215
I left with Lord Benvolio willingly,

06:37.714 --> 06:40.378
to solve the mystery
of who plagues our city...

06:40.734 --> 06:43.452
and we were successful in our efforts.

06:45.246 --> 06:46.877
[Sighs]

06:46.910 --> 06:50.204
It is Paris who plots against you.

06:51.498 --> 06:54.793
You speak of this "New Prince"...

06:54.818 --> 06:56.900
it must be him.

06:57.854 --> 06:59.361
Count Paris?

07:00.190 --> 07:02.620
He bade me to lie to you
about Benvolio...

07:03.298 --> 07:04.892
or Livia would pay with her life.

07:04.926 --> 07:07.285
And yet you tell me now...

07:07.998 --> 07:11.611
I knew you wanted to be alone with me...

07:12.040 --> 07:16.955
and I know he has supporters
throughout the city,

07:17.428 --> 07:18.833
hidden though they may be.

07:18.867 --> 07:20.423
So you use me...

07:21.268 --> 07:22.961
my feelings for you...

07:22.995 --> 07:25.617
to spin some story
that Count Paris of Mantua,

07:25.650 --> 07:27.249
a man I've known
since we were children...

07:27.283 --> 07:30.141
None of us are children anymore!

07:33.495 --> 07:37.140
Benvolio Montague is no murderer,

07:37.174 --> 07:39.234
no traitor to Verona...

07:39.991 --> 07:43.892
I ask that you spare his life.

07:43.926 --> 07:47.413
♪♪

07:47.446 --> 07:49.300
A man whose execution

07:49.335 --> 07:51.668
would stop the war
between your two Houses?

07:51.701 --> 07:54.516
A man whom all Verona
already believes is a kidnapper,

07:54.550 --> 07:56.660
and a murderer, at the very least?

07:56.693 --> 07:59.316
Do <i> you</i> believe that?

07:59.836 --> 08:01.370
I believe...

08:03.461 --> 08:06.147
...that his death is
what this city needs to heal.

08:08.070 --> 08:09.733
And you would kill an innocent man

08:09.767 --> 08:10.628
to achieve that goal?

08:10.662 --> 08:13.252
I have no proof
of Benvolio's innocence...

08:13.286 --> 08:15.684
I only have proof of his guilt.

08:16.271 --> 08:19.555
And the life of one man,
to save a city of thousands?

08:19.951 --> 08:22.510
Tell me that's not a small price
to pay, either way.

08:23.778 --> 08:25.454
What if...

08:25.487 --> 08:28.793
I could find you proof
of Benvolio's innocence...

08:28.828 --> 08:31.885
- [Scoffs]
- ...and proof of this New Prince?

08:32.807 --> 08:34.673
Enough to unite the city
without an execution...

08:34.707 --> 08:35.697
Rosaline...

08:35.731 --> 08:38.321
Don't think I didn't hear you.

08:39.628 --> 08:44.337
Don't think I haven't <i> longed</i>
for you to say those words.

08:45.044 --> 08:46.417
I have.

08:51.122 --> 08:52.592
And yet?

08:53.224 --> 08:55.023
And yet,

08:55.058 --> 08:59.230
it was your decree that
made me a friend of my enemy.

09:00.830 --> 09:04.879
A Capulet begging
for a Montague's life...

09:05.628 --> 09:08.666
isn't that everything
you had hoped to achieve?

09:10.973 --> 09:13.018
Give me a day.

09:13.053 --> 09:14.875
One day.

09:14.909 --> 09:18.458
And if I can't prove everything I said,

09:19.017 --> 09:20.871
I'll pursue it no further.

09:23.562 --> 09:25.383
[Sighs]

09:25.418 --> 09:26.568
One day.

09:26.601 --> 09:28.651
One day.

09:28.676 --> 09:31.586
♪♪

09:36.274 --> 09:37.743
[Whispers] Thank you.

09:39.000 --> 09:45.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

09:49.983 --> 09:50.941
Brother...

09:50.974 --> 09:51.901
Isabella.

09:51.934 --> 09:53.702
Welcome home.

09:55.267 --> 09:58.241
We are glad to have you back
safely in Verona, my Princess.

09:58.276 --> 09:59.681
What has happened in my absence?

09:59.715 --> 10:01.697
We saw the smoke from
the cathedral as we arrived,

10:01.731 --> 10:04.898
and it said Lord Montague is
gathering his men for revenge...

10:04.931 --> 10:06.923
A bump on the road to peace.

10:07.519 --> 10:10.206
Fear not, sister... I have a plan.

10:10.307 --> 10:12.161
Have you heard Benvolio Montague rots

10:12.195 --> 10:13.537
in our dungeon as we speak?

10:14.431 --> 10:16.033
Did you find Rosaline?

10:16.067 --> 10:17.440
- Is she...
- Safe,

10:17.475 --> 10:19.041
and with her family.

10:19.074 --> 10:20.107
[Sighs]

10:20.142 --> 10:23.073
All thanks to Count Paris of Mantua.

10:24.130 --> 10:27.296
Now, I hear you bear good tidings.

10:28.294 --> 10:31.573
The treaty with Venice has been signed.

10:35.250 --> 10:36.536
Well done.

10:37.543 --> 10:39.716
A victory for Verona.

10:39.750 --> 10:40.808
I'll tell you the whole story

10:40.842 --> 10:42.708
once I've rested from my journey.

10:42.733 --> 10:44.836
But congratulations, Brother...

10:45.189 --> 10:47.524
seems you have the city well in hand.

10:51.328 --> 10:53.183
A plan, Your Grace?

10:54.693 --> 10:55.972
For peace.

10:57.546 --> 10:59.400
Give me a day, Abbatelli.

10:59.622 --> 11:00.963
[Sighs]

11:00.997 --> 11:03.140
Just one day.

11:03.173 --> 11:06.084
♪♪

11:09.669 --> 11:12.195
Dungeon Master: I will be
right outside, my Lady.

11:12.230 --> 11:15.331
♪♪

11:17.828 --> 11:19.746
Here to take the knife from my back?

11:21.014 --> 11:22.864
- I know you're angry with me...
- No,

11:22.899 --> 11:24.675
I'm angry at myself.

11:25.116 --> 11:27.385
For not knowing better
than to trust a Capulet.

11:27.891 --> 11:29.282
I had no choice.

11:30.017 --> 11:32.473
If I hadn't done exactly as Paris said,

11:32.508 --> 11:34.745
we'd have all been killed.

11:35.164 --> 11:36.409
And my sister, too.

11:37.931 --> 11:39.193
Your sister?

11:39.603 --> 11:40.976
Paris threatened her...

11:41.010 --> 11:43.536
<i>is</i> threatening her.

11:43.570 --> 11:45.327
And I couldn't risk her life.

11:45.939 --> 11:47.761
I see.

11:47.794 --> 11:50.704
So you chose to kill me off, instead.

11:50.738 --> 11:53.369
♪♪

11:53.394 --> 11:55.728
I've told the Prince the truth now.

11:58.648 --> 12:00.598
But he needs proof.

12:02.129 --> 12:04.367
Remember what Friar Lawrence said?

12:04.958 --> 12:07.280
That it was the Nurse
who confessed to him?

12:07.857 --> 12:09.391
If I can convince her

12:09.425 --> 12:11.506
to tell the Prince what she knows,

12:12.890 --> 12:13.944
you'll be freed.

12:17.456 --> 12:21.423
Nothing has changed.

12:21.716 --> 12:23.378
I'm still your friend.

12:29.544 --> 12:30.758
Very well.

12:31.401 --> 12:34.309
But if you're going to save me, Capulet,

12:34.344 --> 12:36.422
I suggest you hurry.

12:36.456 --> 12:39.334
♪♪

12:43.935 --> 12:45.693
[Door closes]

12:45.727 --> 12:46.749
Rosaline: Nurse!

12:46.783 --> 12:48.540
What are you doing awake?

12:48.574 --> 12:49.404
Looking for you.

12:49.438 --> 12:50.460
Oh, come along.

12:50.494 --> 12:53.405
Friar Lawrence told me
everything you confessed to him.

12:53.438 --> 12:55.325
♪♪

12:55.358 --> 12:56.605
He broke the holy seal?

12:56.638 --> 12:58.813
The secrets you keep for my aunt.

12:58.846 --> 13:01.693
Hiding Paris
beneath my uncle's own roof,

13:01.726 --> 13:05.226
sitting silent as they plotted
murder and mayhem.

13:06.333 --> 13:09.500
You <i> must</i> tell Prince Escalus
what you know...

13:10.078 --> 13:11.550
I cannot.

13:11.584 --> 13:13.212
[Breathing shakily] Lady Capulet...

13:13.247 --> 13:16.529
- Is a monster.
- Is my mistress.

13:17.246 --> 13:19.805
I beg you, forget what you know...

13:22.590 --> 13:25.788
You let that man seduce my sister.

13:25.822 --> 13:28.187
She cannot see him for what he is.

13:28.221 --> 13:31.675
But I do. And this will go no further.

13:31.710 --> 13:34.171
Let me sleep on it.

13:34.205 --> 13:35.836
We don't have time...

13:36.466 --> 13:39.515
You're asking me to turn my back
on someone I've loved

13:39.886 --> 13:41.721
since the day she was born.

13:43.261 --> 13:45.563
You can have your answer in the morning.

13:45.597 --> 13:49.435
♪♪

13:49.649 --> 13:51.022
[Door opens]

13:58.824 --> 14:00.358
[Lady Capulet screams]

14:02.504 --> 14:04.038
Oh, my God.

14:07.113 --> 14:08.646
Oh, my God.

14:08.680 --> 14:11.110
Someone!

14:11.144 --> 14:13.190
What on Earth are you shouting about

14:13.224 --> 14:14.950
at this time of the...

14:14.984 --> 14:16.166
Dear God...

14:18.184 --> 14:19.270
Is she dead?

14:19.303 --> 14:22.853
♪♪

14:23.667 --> 14:25.520
Please tell me she's not dead.

14:31.956 --> 14:34.269
Oh, God. Oh... Oh, God.

14:34.304 --> 14:35.603
Oh, my God.

14:35.637 --> 14:39.123
♪♪

14:44.592 --> 14:47.929
I'll... fetch someone to, uh...

14:48.471 --> 14:50.261
put her to bed.

14:50.295 --> 14:51.700
I'll stay with her.

14:52.625 --> 14:54.005
Thank you.

14:54.999 --> 14:59.116
[Door opens, closes]

14:59.150 --> 15:00.884
I didn't think you'd take it <i> this</i> hard.

15:00.918 --> 15:04.244
♪♪

15:04.279 --> 15:05.877
[Inhales sharply]

15:06.442 --> 15:07.816
You did this?

15:08.061 --> 15:09.609
She was going to go to the Prince.

15:09.643 --> 15:13.321
Tell him everything.
All at Rosaline's behest.

15:13.621 --> 15:15.315
You wouldn't let me kill your niece.

15:15.349 --> 15:16.628
This was the next best thing.

15:16.661 --> 15:18.771
[Breathing heavily]

15:19.231 --> 15:20.893
Th... That woman took care of me

15:20.927 --> 15:23.420
from the moment I entered this world.

15:23.455 --> 15:25.908
Do you want to be drawn and quartered?

15:26.943 --> 15:28.220
'Cause I don't.

15:29.663 --> 15:31.516
Coups are never bloodless.

15:31.550 --> 15:33.212
Let's not pretend they are.

15:33.246 --> 15:36.348
♪♪

15:38.671 --> 15:40.925
Lady Rosaline, your Grace.

15:41.819 --> 15:43.262
Leave us.

15:49.913 --> 15:51.383
Did you find it?

15:51.417 --> 15:53.047
Your proof?

15:54.812 --> 15:55.991
No.

15:56.025 --> 15:58.103
Time is up. I'm sorry.

15:58.775 --> 16:00.023
I doubt that.

16:00.057 --> 16:01.687
[Sighs]

16:04.130 --> 16:05.407
You have to let this go.

16:05.441 --> 16:07.775
- I will never...
- You were on your own,

16:07.810 --> 16:10.172
outside the city walls, with a man.

16:10.439 --> 16:12.742
If you don't stop this crusade,
there will be talk...

16:12.776 --> 16:14.582
Of what...

16:15.303 --> 16:17.001
my virtue?

16:17.768 --> 16:21.607
Do you care more for my honor
than an innocent man's life?

16:21.642 --> 16:23.302
What more would you have me do?

16:23.816 --> 16:26.598
I've given you every chance
to find me proof...

16:28.520 --> 16:31.462
Because my word isn't proof enough.

16:31.496 --> 16:33.990
♪♪

16:34.660 --> 16:35.650
Rosaline...

16:36.145 --> 16:37.522
Rosaline!

16:39.300 --> 16:40.225
[Sighs]

16:40.260 --> 16:43.042
♪♪

16:50.240 --> 16:51.806
You expect me to sign a truce

16:51.839 --> 16:53.917
with the man
who burned down my cathedral?!

16:53.952 --> 16:56.190
Lord Capulet: Your Grace,
the Duomo has been in my family

16:56.224 --> 16:57.438
for three generations.

16:57.472 --> 16:59.166
Frankly, it was mine to burn.

16:59.200 --> 17:01.245
The Princess took it from you
and gave it to me.

17:01.280 --> 17:03.645
Because you were too poor to finish it.

17:03.679 --> 17:05.724
Lord Montague, your nephew Benvolio

17:05.759 --> 17:07.518
has been accused
of leading an insurrection.

17:07.550 --> 17:09.310
A ridiculous charge...

17:09.344 --> 17:10.717
We have witnesses.

17:10.751 --> 17:12.444
Evidence.

17:12.865 --> 17:15.167
He is a stain upon your family name.

17:15.202 --> 17:17.823
And most rulers would
order your House disbanded

17:17.858 --> 17:19.135
over an act of treason.

17:19.605 --> 17:22.143
Your wealth would revert to the Crown.

17:22.176 --> 17:23.742
Your family would return to the fields

17:23.777 --> 17:24.991
where they once toiled.

17:25.528 --> 17:27.839
Lord Capulet's fields, I believe.

17:30.967 --> 17:32.662
You are merciful, Your Grace.

17:33.286 --> 17:35.037
Indeed.

17:35.479 --> 17:39.220
Instead, Young Montague
will be executed for his crimes.

17:39.255 --> 17:41.813
In this way, Lord Capulet
will have vengeance

17:41.846 --> 17:43.413
for the murder of Gramio Capulet

17:43.447 --> 17:45.301
and the kidnapping of Lady Rosaline,

17:45.335 --> 17:47.029
and you, Lord Montague,

17:47.064 --> 17:50.132
will have sacrificed your heir
to appease the Crown.

17:50.166 --> 17:52.373
Your family's slate will be wiped clean.

17:52.406 --> 17:55.253
And your Houses will be at peace.

17:56.694 --> 17:59.061
This document lays out
the terms of your truce.

17:59.095 --> 18:00.468
And it is binding.

18:00.892 --> 18:02.298
Are we agreed?

18:02.332 --> 18:04.066
The Capulets agree.

18:04.988 --> 18:06.521
[Scribbling]

18:06.556 --> 18:09.337
♪♪

18:12.283 --> 18:15.546
His Grace is being more
than generous, Lord Montague.

18:19.451 --> 18:20.985
The Montagues agree.

18:23.227 --> 18:26.839
Then may this be the first
of many agreements between you.

18:33.307 --> 18:35.576
She was the one person in this House

18:35.610 --> 18:39.193
who was always kind to Rosaline and me.

18:39.977 --> 18:41.520
I loved her.

18:55.192 --> 18:56.374
I have a proposal for you.

18:56.408 --> 18:57.526
[Chuckles]

18:57.560 --> 19:00.310
Did you not already propose to me?

19:00.344 --> 19:02.679
Do you want to hear my answer again?

19:02.712 --> 19:04.599
I promise, it'll be the same.

19:04.935 --> 19:06.277
We should run off together.

19:06.311 --> 19:08.069
[Laughing] What?

19:08.104 --> 19:09.828
We should run way.

19:09.863 --> 19:11.141
Now.

19:11.175 --> 19:12.516
Today.

19:12.551 --> 19:15.973
♪♪

19:16.007 --> 19:17.829
We can't just elope...

19:17.863 --> 19:18.987
Why not?

19:19.196 --> 19:21.042
Your sister's back, safe and sound.

19:21.077 --> 19:22.579
Your Uncle gave his consent...

19:24.980 --> 19:27.322
Our lives on this Earth are short.

19:28.119 --> 19:30.037
Look no further than your beloved Nurse.

19:38.486 --> 19:40.671
Lady Rosaline! Have you heard the news?

19:40.719 --> 19:42.067
What news?

19:42.101 --> 19:45.491
- Your sister...
- she's eloped with Count Paris!

19:45.525 --> 19:47.571
[Sighs] Isn't it romantic?!

19:47.605 --> 19:50.035
♪♪

19:50.069 --> 19:51.316
[Exhales shakily]

19:51.779 --> 19:54.241
- This is your fault!
- My fault?

19:54.275 --> 19:55.745
I know you hate me. But Livia?

19:55.778 --> 19:57.696
What on Earth has she ever done to you?

19:57.731 --> 20:00.000
I only wanted
what was best for the girl.

20:00.034 --> 20:02.601
Then why offer her up to that animal?

20:03.874 --> 20:05.601
Paris would never harm your sister.

20:05.634 --> 20:09.389
Oh, just like he would
never harm the Nurse?

20:09.917 --> 20:13.529
Or are we still to pretend
she fell down the stairs?

20:15.511 --> 20:19.125
Juliet would be ashamed of you.

20:19.150 --> 20:20.940
♪♪

20:21.629 --> 20:23.356
Remember that.

20:28.957 --> 20:31.334
This is a good thing, Damiano...

20:31.387 --> 20:33.433
Leave me, Tessa... I'm in no mood.

20:33.467 --> 20:34.937
Benvolio is a lost cause.

20:34.971 --> 20:36.985
Who should not have lived
to see this day.

20:37.019 --> 20:39.160
You shut your mouth.

20:39.195 --> 20:41.015
I will not.

20:42.658 --> 20:46.239
Do you forget the pact
that we made in this very room?

20:46.274 --> 20:48.223
With our brother Agostino

20:48.257 --> 20:51.743
sleeping peacefully in his chambers,

20:51.778 --> 20:54.432
never knowing that his next meal
would be his last?

20:56.098 --> 20:57.215
Do you forget

20:57.250 --> 20:59.295
what you swore to me that night?

20:59.330 --> 21:02.367
When you showed me the poison
that you bought from that Friar,

21:02.401 --> 21:04.735
and you told me
what you planned to do with it?

21:05.890 --> 21:07.871
"When I'm Lord Montague,

21:07.905 --> 21:10.451
this shall be <i> our</i> House,
sister," you said.

21:10.485 --> 21:13.089
"Yours and mine, together."

21:14.448 --> 21:15.791
Though it won't be for long

21:15.816 --> 21:17.593
if you don't take the Prince's offer.

21:18.434 --> 21:21.197
And all because of Benvolio.

21:21.222 --> 21:23.555
How it must haunt you
to think it was you

21:23.580 --> 21:25.210
who spared his young life.

21:25.235 --> 21:26.929
He was an innocent child...

21:26.954 --> 21:29.512
Who became the man
who took down your House.

21:29.954 --> 21:33.024
Benvolio's death will benefit us all...

21:33.058 --> 21:35.204
Montagues and Capulets alike.

21:35.239 --> 21:36.695
And...

21:37.457 --> 21:40.398
I'd hate for the world to know
what happened in this room

21:40.423 --> 21:42.117
those many years ago.

21:42.535 --> 21:44.383
Wouldn't you...

21:44.417 --> 21:46.175
Lord Montague?

21:46.209 --> 21:49.535
♪♪

21:53.089 --> 21:56.798
No guards. No courtiers. No witnesses.

21:56.832 --> 21:59.135
I doubt you've brought me here
to plead my case.

21:59.777 --> 22:01.375
I've brought you here because

22:01.408 --> 22:03.639
I hope to make sense
of something before you die.

22:04.932 --> 22:06.574
I know the Montagues well.

22:06.608 --> 22:08.640
And you, Benvolio,

22:08.674 --> 22:10.831
are nothing more
than a gutter scoundrel.

22:11.284 --> 22:12.735
Unprincipled, undisciplined...

22:12.768 --> 22:14.462
Often drunk.

22:15.841 --> 22:18.174
So why is it that the only person

22:18.208 --> 22:19.711
fighting for your life

22:19.744 --> 22:21.662
is a woman you took from her home...

22:23.296 --> 22:24.670
...whose honor must now and forever

22:24.704 --> 22:26.014
be held in question...

22:26.048 --> 22:27.806
a woman who should hate you more

22:27.840 --> 22:29.534
than any man on Earth?

22:31.520 --> 22:34.782
Because Rosaline Capulet is my friend.

22:35.202 --> 22:37.247
I trust her. And she trusts me.

22:39.233 --> 22:40.959
You've tricked her into trusting you.

22:41.302 --> 22:43.103
How?

22:43.137 --> 22:44.305
I don't know.

22:45.973 --> 22:48.031
But she does.

22:49.502 --> 22:51.514
Tell Rosaline you seek to overthrow me.

22:51.922 --> 22:53.688
That you call yourself the New Prince.

22:53.723 --> 22:55.984
And that you are a traitor to Verona.

22:56.275 --> 22:58.128
No.

22:58.671 --> 23:00.079
[Scoffs]

23:00.114 --> 23:01.680
[Grunts]

23:01.714 --> 23:04.464
Until she hears it from you,
she will not rest.

23:04.497 --> 23:07.568
She will destroy her name.
Her reputation. Her future.

23:07.602 --> 23:10.064
You have ruined your life, Montague.

23:10.098 --> 23:12.016
I will not let you ruin Rosaline's, too.

23:12.050 --> 23:13.519
[Both grunt]

23:13.554 --> 23:16.125
Kill me today, or kill me tomorrow!

23:16.395 --> 23:18.153
It matters not to me.

23:18.187 --> 23:20.393
But I will never lie to her.

23:22.311 --> 23:24.710
That is why she trusts me.

23:24.735 --> 23:27.388
♪♪

23:27.500 --> 23:29.449
Matteo!

23:34.177 --> 23:35.679
Take him away!

23:45.466 --> 23:47.097
I have business at the Palace.

23:47.130 --> 23:49.177
So whatever you want,

23:49.211 --> 23:50.392
make it quick.

23:50.427 --> 23:51.481
How strange

23:51.514 --> 23:53.944
that you have business anywhere.

23:55.227 --> 23:56.921
Considering you're dead.

23:58.212 --> 23:59.640
What are you talking about?

24:00.422 --> 24:02.583
It seems you neglected to mention

24:02.618 --> 24:05.720
a few details
about your time in Scotland...

24:06.679 --> 24:07.801
Vicious lies...

24:07.834 --> 24:11.416
I wonder how King Malcolm
might respond if he knew.

24:11.701 --> 24:13.715
Might he take your head off, too?

24:13.749 --> 24:14.963
[Cup thuds]

24:14.997 --> 24:18.995
♪♪

24:19.028 --> 24:21.074
I'm somewhat more merciful than you are

24:21.109 --> 24:22.802
when it comes to blood relations.

24:22.837 --> 24:26.462
So I won't sell you out,
<i>if</i> you leave here. Now.

24:26.497 --> 24:29.805
And never grace this doorstep...
or anywhere in Verona...

24:29.843 --> 24:31.377
with your presence again.

24:33.138 --> 24:37.361
And take that <i> awful</i> painting with you.

24:37.395 --> 24:40.048
♪♪

24:45.714 --> 24:47.696
[Footsteps approaching]

24:51.315 --> 24:53.040
Aunt Tessa?

24:53.074 --> 24:55.376
Sweet Benvolio.

24:55.410 --> 24:57.936
What a pity it is
to see you in this place.

24:59.023 --> 25:00.337
What are you doing here?

25:02.192 --> 25:05.531
I think a man deserves
to know the truth about his life

25:05.565 --> 25:06.960
before he dies.

25:07.593 --> 25:09.287
Don't you?

25:18.161 --> 25:20.048
Giuliana.

25:20.081 --> 25:21.327
Why are you not in bed?

25:21.361 --> 25:23.343
[Inhales deeply]

25:23.377 --> 25:25.008
Juliet...

25:25.341 --> 25:27.056
What of her?

25:28.465 --> 25:29.871
[Inhales deeply]

25:29.906 --> 25:31.983
I know the meaning of her warnings.

25:32.017 --> 25:35.279
♪♪

25:38.013 --> 25:40.604
I know why she says "beware."

25:42.358 --> 25:43.503
You do?

25:43.984 --> 25:45.085
Yes.

25:47.398 --> 25:49.028
Silvestro.

25:50.837 --> 25:52.594
I've done a terrible thing.

26:01.376 --> 26:04.387
[Chuckles] I never knew
I could be so happy.

26:04.421 --> 26:05.790
Nor I. My love.

26:11.824 --> 26:12.750
[Both moan]

26:15.664 --> 26:17.934
- Forgive me.
- I must send word to Mantua.

26:17.968 --> 26:20.910
No, stay...

26:22.844 --> 26:24.154
I won't be long.

26:27.306 --> 26:28.808
Keep the bed warm.

26:28.842 --> 26:29.768
[Chuckles]

26:36.906 --> 26:38.408
[Door closes]

26:38.442 --> 26:40.360
[Inhales deeply]

27:07.035 --> 27:09.018
Rosaline: <i> Dearest Livia...</i>

27:09.051 --> 27:11.322
<i>I have left with the Montague
to solve the mystery</i>

27:11.356 --> 27:13.050
<i>of who framed him for murder.</i>

27:13.084 --> 27:16.153
♪♪

27:20.091 --> 27:21.290
Uncle.

27:22.076 --> 27:23.609
Is the whole family come to visit me

27:23.643 --> 27:25.625
on the eve of my death?

27:25.659 --> 27:26.841
I'm sorry?

27:27.235 --> 27:29.025
Aunt Tessa was here.

27:34.346 --> 27:35.849
What did she want?

27:35.883 --> 27:38.696
Only to spin some tale of
poisoning my father.

27:39.558 --> 27:41.067
You always said she was a liar...

27:41.092 --> 27:42.659
She is.

27:44.331 --> 27:47.784
Still, a strange way to say goodbye.

27:48.510 --> 27:50.045
Indeed.

27:54.465 --> 27:56.704
Unless it wasn't that strange.

27:56.737 --> 27:59.456
♪♪

28:01.345 --> 28:03.648
Was she lying?

28:03.682 --> 28:05.151
Uncle?

28:05.851 --> 28:08.191
Tessa's mad. Always has been.

28:10.300 --> 28:11.679
Did you kill my father?

28:11.713 --> 28:16.352
♪♪

28:16.385 --> 28:19.391
I always wondered
why I was never good enough.

28:20.324 --> 28:22.050
Why you treated me like I was worthless.

28:22.084 --> 28:23.970
What I could have done
to make you hate me so.

28:24.004 --> 28:26.241
- Benvolio...
- And now I know:

28:26.688 --> 28:28.993
I remind you of the man you murdered.

28:30.659 --> 28:32.130
The irony is, I'm only in this cell

28:32.163 --> 28:34.529
because I was trying to save our House.

28:35.197 --> 28:37.026
Our name.

28:37.059 --> 28:39.649
Unraveling the conspiracy,
hunting down Friar Lawrence...

28:39.683 --> 28:41.408
Friar Lawrence? It doesn't matter.

28:42.329 --> 28:44.520
He's long gone, and he's taken
the truth with him.

28:44.555 --> 28:46.010
What truth?

28:46.897 --> 28:48.503
[Sternly] Leave me.

28:48.537 --> 28:51.488
♪♪

29:02.618 --> 29:04.664
For what it's worth...

29:04.698 --> 29:07.160
I regret how I've always treated you.

29:08.146 --> 29:10.456
Actually, Uncle...

29:10.816 --> 29:13.015
that isn't worth anything to me at all.

29:13.050 --> 29:16.439
♪♪

29:19.043 --> 29:22.227
- [Door opens]
- Isabella: What were you thinking?

29:22.607 --> 29:24.460
I spoke with Abbatelli.

29:24.494 --> 29:26.469
You fought Benvolio, a murderer,

29:26.503 --> 29:27.609
for a <i> woman?</i>

29:27.643 --> 29:28.755
You could have been killed.

29:28.790 --> 29:31.004
Did you think I didn't consider that?

29:31.765 --> 29:32.819
And still, you did it.

29:32.844 --> 29:34.858
I swore a vow to protect my people...

29:34.883 --> 29:36.965
Your guards protect the people.
You protect the throne.

29:36.990 --> 29:38.260
Damn the throne!

29:39.279 --> 29:40.887
Damn all of it!

29:41.550 --> 29:44.653
Without her... I'm nothing.

29:44.686 --> 29:48.387
♪♪

29:48.412 --> 29:50.267
I love her.

29:55.213 --> 29:56.486
I know.

29:57.742 --> 29:59.212
But while you were coming to her rescue,

29:59.245 --> 30:01.835
her family burned
the Montague cathedral.

30:01.869 --> 30:03.435
If you marry her, Escalus,

30:03.470 --> 30:06.411
the Montagues will burn the city
to the ground.

30:06.872 --> 30:07.979
[Sighs]

30:09.613 --> 30:12.753
Strength and sacrifice, brother.

30:16.301 --> 30:19.382
I thought I was doing
what was best for our House...

30:19.417 --> 30:21.387
By committing treason?

30:21.420 --> 30:23.371
Escalus is weak.

30:24.156 --> 30:25.352
When his father died,

30:25.386 --> 30:26.683
I knew it was only a matter of time

30:26.717 --> 30:29.018
before the Montagues
exploited that weakness...

30:29.052 --> 30:30.490
So you thought
you would beat them to it?

30:30.524 --> 30:32.538
By putting Paris on the throne?

30:32.573 --> 30:35.322
A ruler loyal to House Capulet,

30:35.356 --> 30:37.178
to put down House Montague,
once and for all.

30:37.211 --> 30:39.706
Does no part of you see
the value in that?

30:40.697 --> 30:42.234
Of course I do.

30:43.698 --> 30:47.792
But then why did Juliet

30:47.817 --> 30:49.447
try to warn me?

30:53.819 --> 30:55.929
She loved a Montague.

30:59.839 --> 31:01.692
She wanted peace.

31:04.446 --> 31:06.364
You must send a message to Paris.

31:06.399 --> 31:08.124
Tell him to call off his plan.

31:08.158 --> 31:10.780
Oh, it's too far gone.
He's not going to listen to me.

31:10.815 --> 31:12.060
Why on Earth did you think

31:12.094 --> 31:13.404
he would stay loyal to our House?

31:13.439 --> 31:15.323
Because I was a fool!

31:15.938 --> 31:17.757
We must warn the Prince.

31:17.790 --> 31:19.100
Before it's too late.

31:19.134 --> 31:21.884
The Prince will execute me.

31:21.918 --> 31:23.421
Perhaps not,

31:23.454 --> 31:26.827
if you can prove you're loyal
without delay.

31:29.150 --> 31:31.580
Come, Giuliana. We must go.

31:31.614 --> 31:35.131
♪♪

31:35.560 --> 31:36.934
Dear God...

31:36.969 --> 31:38.471
Pietro...

31:38.504 --> 31:40.198
Apologies, my Lord and Lady...

31:40.232 --> 31:41.767
But we cannot allow you to leave.

31:43.273 --> 31:45.126
The New Prince commands it.

31:45.160 --> 31:46.247
[Door opens]

31:46.281 --> 31:48.679
♪♪

31:51.913 --> 31:53.446
[Breathing heavily]

31:57.768 --> 31:59.014
[Door opens]

31:59.484 --> 32:01.285
My love.

32:01.737 --> 32:02.981
My Livia.

32:03.735 --> 32:05.588
What is this?

32:06.992 --> 32:08.901
What does it mean?

32:09.286 --> 32:11.333
This letter says...

32:11.717 --> 32:13.795
Rosaline went with the Montague
willingly...

32:14.051 --> 32:15.617
that she wasn't kidnapped at all.

32:15.642 --> 32:17.464
But I never received it,

32:18.045 --> 32:19.747
and it's here.

32:20.088 --> 32:21.571
With your things.

32:21.606 --> 32:24.579
♪♪

32:28.037 --> 32:30.223
Our love began in secret,

32:32.256 --> 32:34.712
but I don't want there to be
any more secrets between us.

32:35.328 --> 32:37.822
I promised you I'd make you a princess,

32:37.855 --> 32:39.806
and that is true.

32:39.839 --> 32:42.652
The Princess of Mantua...

32:43.455 --> 32:46.429
<i>and</i> of Verona.

32:48.479 --> 32:51.411
But what of Prince Escalus?

32:51.936 --> 32:54.941
My city, my family... are you mad?

32:54.975 --> 32:56.349
♪♪

32:56.725 --> 32:58.388
You lied to me.

32:58.422 --> 33:00.148
- I didn't lie...
- And what,

33:00.181 --> 33:02.035
you thought a Capulet bride

33:02.070 --> 33:04.591
would bring you
some kind of legitimacy...

33:05.621 --> 33:08.243
you thought my blood
would buy you a throne?

33:09.221 --> 33:10.770
I told you... no more secrets.

33:10.805 --> 33:11.987
And I'll be honest with you now...

33:12.021 --> 33:15.315
yes, at first
I thought I needed your name,

33:15.349 --> 33:17.811
but now that I know you,
now that I love you,

33:17.846 --> 33:20.482
- Livia...
- Rosaline knew.

33:21.429 --> 33:23.136
She tried to warn me...

33:23.161 --> 33:25.687
Just listen to me...

33:25.712 --> 33:28.141
[Voice breaking] I gave myself to you.

33:28.176 --> 33:29.454
And you will again.

33:29.488 --> 33:30.958
[Sniffles]

33:30.992 --> 33:33.294
Once... Once you understand.

33:34.767 --> 33:36.494
Now gather your things.

33:36.528 --> 33:37.838
My men will bring you to Mantua.

33:37.872 --> 33:39.246
I want to go home.

33:39.280 --> 33:42.541
[Sternly] <i>Mantua</i> is your home now.

33:43.407 --> 33:44.590
Wife.

33:47.854 --> 33:50.700
[Key jangling, door opens]

33:51.726 --> 33:53.580
Capulet.

33:53.614 --> 33:55.372
What news?

33:58.270 --> 34:00.684
I thought I had proof...

34:01.773 --> 34:05.485
I thought the Nurse would come forward

34:06.318 --> 34:10.539
[voice breaking]
but then Paris killed her,

34:12.117 --> 34:14.705
and he has my sister,

34:16.059 --> 34:17.408
and...

34:19.614 --> 34:21.629
...I failed you.

34:23.520 --> 34:28.126
And I'm so, so sorry.

34:29.667 --> 34:31.585
This is all my fault.

34:33.150 --> 34:34.364
No matter.

34:36.358 --> 34:37.924
No matter?!

34:40.161 --> 34:44.063
I was foolish enough to think
I could heal our city...

34:44.097 --> 34:46.132
make my cousin's death mean something,

34:46.166 --> 34:48.831
be a worthy heir to my cursed name.

34:48.864 --> 34:51.838
You mustn't give up.

34:51.871 --> 34:53.726
Perhaps when they kill me,

34:53.760 --> 34:55.967
Verona might be healed.

34:56.001 --> 34:58.110
And you can go and be happy...

34:59.139 --> 35:00.756
I won't...

35:01.669 --> 35:03.875
be happy.

35:04.586 --> 35:09.086
Leave me and let me die, Capulet.

35:09.741 --> 35:11.582
I'm not what you want.

35:12.277 --> 35:13.918
I'm not who you want...

35:15.221 --> 35:16.890
I saw you.

35:18.366 --> 35:19.612
In the chapel,

35:19.645 --> 35:21.308
when he told us we were to be married,

35:21.342 --> 35:23.228
I saw you.

35:23.262 --> 35:25.065
The two of you.

35:26.334 --> 35:28.955
The Prince loves you.

35:29.778 --> 35:31.488
And you love him.

35:32.906 --> 35:34.950
<i>That</i> is who you want.

35:36.201 --> 35:37.979
That is who you love.

35:40.098 --> 35:41.748
That is who you trust.

35:52.006 --> 35:54.717
I trust you.

35:54.751 --> 35:57.082
♪♪

36:27.529 --> 36:29.799
[Door opens] Dungeon Master: Time's up.

36:30.345 --> 36:32.454
[Exhales deeply]

36:32.489 --> 36:35.367
♪♪

36:45.165 --> 36:47.531
[Indistinct chatter]

36:55.298 --> 36:59.424
On this day, we reclaim our city...

36:59.909 --> 37:03.233
and this square... from violence

37:03.266 --> 37:06.113
and stand together as one.

37:06.146 --> 37:08.289
[Praying indistinctly]
By the Prince's order,

37:08.322 --> 37:13.024
the traitor Benvolio Montague
shall be executed,

37:13.057 --> 37:15.743
for the murder of Gramio Capulet,

37:15.777 --> 37:18.592
the kidnapping of Rosaline Capulet,

37:18.625 --> 37:22.604
and for high crimes
against the city of Verona.

37:22.638 --> 37:24.237
[Sobs]

37:24.271 --> 37:25.664
[Indistinct shouting]

37:28.641 --> 37:30.495
And with his death,

37:30.529 --> 37:34.267
the Houses of Montague and Capulet

37:34.301 --> 37:36.327
have sworn to their sovereign

37:36.361 --> 37:40.607
to lay down their arms forevermore.

37:40.641 --> 37:43.199
[Indistinct shouting]

38:12.350 --> 38:14.460
Justice, or vengeance?

38:14.495 --> 38:17.884
We're here now, Brother. Does it matter?

38:19.646 --> 38:21.074
It does.

38:22.046 --> 38:23.356
To me.

38:23.390 --> 38:26.812
[Shouting continues]

38:26.846 --> 38:29.980
♪♪

38:35.166 --> 38:36.507
Wait!

38:37.169 --> 38:38.704
Wait!

38:38.729 --> 38:39.879
[Shouting stops]

38:46.686 --> 38:49.083
[Murmuring]

39:05.647 --> 39:06.861
Make him stand.

39:19.691 --> 39:21.833
[Shouting resumes]

39:37.266 --> 39:38.576
Silence!

39:38.739 --> 39:40.236
Silence!

39:41.713 --> 39:42.990
I have been told...

39:43.024 --> 39:46.255
- that this is an innocent man.
- [Murmuring]

39:46.289 --> 39:47.630
We are to believe this innocence

39:47.664 --> 39:49.454
because I trust the word of a person

39:49.488 --> 39:51.886
who stood for Benvolio Montague.

39:51.921 --> 39:53.711
And by my royal command,

39:53.744 --> 39:56.174
you shall endeavor to trust it, too.

39:56.208 --> 39:59.215
Trust the word of a Capulet
who stood for a Montague.

39:59.248 --> 40:01.391
Fiend: The New Prince is coming!

40:01.424 --> 40:03.757
[Crowd screaming]

40:07.614 --> 40:09.020
[Grunts]

40:12.265 --> 40:13.382
The New Prince is coming!

40:13.416 --> 40:14.502
[Arrow whistles]

40:14.536 --> 40:16.198
The New Prince is coming!

40:16.233 --> 40:18.151
Aah!

40:18.184 --> 40:20.198
[Screaming continues]

40:20.232 --> 40:23.110
♪♪

40:32.377 --> 40:33.782
Escalus!

40:33.817 --> 40:34.883
[Screams]

40:44.663 --> 40:45.813
Move!

40:49.501 --> 40:51.419
Escalus!

40:51.453 --> 40:52.668
Rosaline.

40:52.701 --> 40:54.748
Rosaline, we need
to get out of here. Now.

40:54.782 --> 40:56.589
- I'm not leaving here without him.
- [Groans]

40:56.623 --> 40:58.299
And I'm not leaving without you.

40:58.333 --> 41:00.668
Take her. Save her.

41:00.702 --> 41:03.580
♪♪

41:12.762 --> 41:14.264
The New Prince is coming!

41:14.298 --> 41:15.608
The New Prince is coming!

41:15.642 --> 41:17.111
The New Prince is coming!

41:17.146 --> 41:19.320
The New Prince is coming!

41:23.065 --> 41:25.303
The New Prince is here.

